messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /api/articles/{slug}
- All HTTP methods acceptable: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The ArticleRetrieve endpoint is registered only for GET on the path "/:slug" within the ArticlesAnonymousRegister group, which is under the articles prefix. In common realworld Gin projects, article routes are mounted under /api/articles, so the full path becomes /api/articles/{slug}.
- The code for ArticleRetrieve explicitly handles only GET requests for this route. There is a special case where if the slug equals "feed", it calls ArticleFeed, but this logic still runs under GET. No other HTTP methods (POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.) are wired to this path in the provided code, so they are not acceptable for this endpoint.
